Gamma of Mauritius Gains Most in Seven Weeks as Profit Surges

-- B y   K a m l e s h   B h u c k o r y
-- 
2011-09-29T10:33:11Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-29/gamma-of-mauritius-gains-most-in-seven-weeks-as-profit-surges.html
Gamma Civic Ltd. (GML) , a Mauritian group
with interests in construction and the nation’s lottery,
advanced the most in seven weeks after saying profit surged
fivefold for its financial year through June.  The stock gained 4.2 percent or 16 rupees to 395 rupees,
the biggest rally since Aug. 10, according to data compiled by
Bloomberg, and closed at its highest since Sept. 05.  Profit increased to 810.2 million rupees ($28 million)
compared with 161.3 million rupees a year earlier, the company
said in a  statement  published on the Port Louis-based Stock
Exchange of Mauritius’s website today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
